title: Hillsboro Classic (Omnium)
description: ZiaVelo Racing Club Presents Las Cruces Time Trial & Hillsboro Classic RR Omnium New Mexico Cup Series (NMCS) #1 – Saturday March 8th & Sunday March 9th, 2008
course:
Saturday 8th – Time Trial Categories P/1/2; 3; 4; 5; Collegiate (same course) is an out and back course on a Frontage Road for 20K (12 miles). Course is mostly flat and straight. 
Sunday 9th – Road Race (see maps in flyer) Categories 4; 5; Juniors; & Collegiate B racers – The 35 mile course starts in Hillsboro toward Lake Valley for 13 miles; returns to Hillsboro finishes with 9 miles up to Kingston.

Categories P/1/2 (Male/Female); 3; Master’s (M); & Collegiate A racers – The 57 mile course starts in Hillsboro toward Lake Valley then continues for 24 miles; returns to Hillsboro and finish with 9 miles up to Kingston.
registration:
Registration: Time Trial event $20; Road Race event $25 (OMNIUM $40.00). One-day license $10/day
		No entry fee for Junior riders (but must have a license or one-day license). 
$5 LATE REGISTRATION FEE per event (Applications received after Tuesday, March 4th, 2008)
notes:
Checks Payable to: ZiaVelo Racing Club; 108 Capri Rd; Las Cruces, NM; 88005
Races Held Wind, Rain, or Shine.  Held under USA Cycling USAC permit. 
Questions:  call Dave Rutledge at 575-541-8271

Lodging: In Hillsboro/Kingston Camping is available at Lakeview RV Park on the east side of I-25, exit #63.   For further information call: 505-743-2242. Additional lodging is available in T or C, about 1 miles north of race registration. Super 8 Motel Truth or Consequences - 505 894-7888; Comfort Inn and Suites Truth or Consequences - 505 894-1660.
directions:
Directions (See map in flyer):
Saturday 8th – Las Cruces STAGING & REGISTRATION – From Las Cruces, take I-10 west to exit #132. Enter Frontage Road travel ¼ mile to REA Road.


Sunday 9th – Hillsboro STAGING & REGISTRATION - From Albuquerque, take I-25 south until you hit the Hillsboro exit #63 (south of T or C).  From Las Cruces, go north on I-25 to exit #63 (north of Hatch).  Parking: In Hillsboro. There are several houses in this area, so please be careful to allow them plenty of access to their homes.  

Updated information at http://ziavelo.googlepages.com/zv-hillsboro
